## Key Guardrails

- Stage gate before any code edit: change doc → wave admission → Prepare wave
- Never commit without explicit operator instruction in the current session
- Seed edits require `seed_edit_allowed` guard approval
- Framework maintenance edits require `framework_edit_allowed` guard approval

## After File Edits

**Agents:** Prefer MCP **`wave_validate`** (and **`wave_garden`** when metadata needs refresh) over shelling out to docs launchers.

The `afterFileEdit` hook runs docs-lint (via the rendered hook `.py` body, which calls `docs_lint.py` directly) after any edit to `docs/`. Fix failures before continuing. Manual CLI fallback: **`wf docs-lint`**.
